I apologize for the confusion. It appears that the `init` method is unavailable for the `INUIAddVoiceShortcutButton` class. In this case, you can use the class method `createWithType:` instead. Here's how to modify the code snippet:

```objective-c
43 | - (NSDictionary *)constantsToExport
44 | {
> 45 |     INUIAddVoiceShortcutButton *button = [INUIAddVoiceShortcutButton buttonWithType:INUIAddVoiceShortcutButtonTypeWhite];
46 |     button.translatesAutoresizingMaskIntoConstraints = NO;
47 |     [button layoutIfNeeded];
48 | }
```

In this example, I used `INUIAddVoiceShortcutButtonTypeWhite` as the button type. You can replace it with any of the available button types:

- `INUIAddVoiceShortcutButtonTypeWhite`
- `INUIAddVoiceShortcutButtonTypeWhiteOutline`
- `INUIAddVoiceShortcutButtonTypeBlack`
- `INUIAddVoiceShortcutButtonTypeBlackOutline`

After making this change, try building the project again.

My apologies for the confusion earlier. It seems I provided incorrect information. You should actually use the `initWithStyle:` method to create a new `INUIAddVoiceShortcutButton`. Here's the correct code snippet:

```objective-c
43 | - (NSDictionary *)constantsToExport
44 | {
> 45 |     INUIAddVoiceShortcutButton *button = [[INUIAddVoiceShortcutButton alloc] initWithStyle:INUIAddVoiceShortcutButtonStyleWhite];
46 |     button.translatesAutoresizingMaskIntoConstraints = NO;
47 |     [button layoutIfNeeded];
48 | }
```

In this example, I used `INUIAddVoiceShortcutButtonStyleWhite` as the button style. You can replace it with any of the available button styles:

- `INUIAddVoiceShortcutButtonStyleWhite`
- `INUIAddVoiceShortcutButtonStyleWhiteOutline`
- `INUIAddVoiceShortcutButtonStyleBlack`
- `INUIAddVoiceShortcutButtonStyleBlackOutline`

This should resolve the warning about implicit conversion between enumeration types and allow your project to build successfully.

